<paragraph blockId="143.[135,787,1539,1884]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis box="[163,224,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">Notes.</emphasis>
– 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="G-BOIS" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<bibRefCitation author="MEYER, F. K." box="[247,443,1539,1563]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" refId="ref141500" refString="MEYER, F. K. (2006 c). Kritische Revision der &quot; Thlaspi &quot; - Arten Europas, Afrikas und Vorderasiens. Spezieller Teil. IX. Noccaea Moench. Haussknechtia Beih. 12." type="book" year="2006">MEYER (2006c: 51)</bibRefCitation>
, followed by AL-SHEHBAZ (2014: 45), overlooked the fact that 
<specimenCount box="[451,593,1572,1596]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
were cited in the original publication of 
<taxonomicName box="[384,601,1604,1628]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis box="[384,601,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">Aethionema rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They recognized the 
<emphasis box="[178,297,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
Kotschy 
<quantity box="[261,297,1635,1659]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" unit="in" value="160.0">160</quantity>
</emphasis>
in 
<collectionCode box="[332,429,1636,1660]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">G-BOIS</collectionCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[506,603,1636,1660]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">holotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="143.[135,787,1539,1884]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
By contrast, 
<bibRefCitation author="HEDGE, I. C." box="[295,494,1667,1692]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" pagination="193 - 493" refId="ref139534" refString="HEDGE, I. C. (1965). Cardamine, Conringia, Iberis, Heldreichia, Aethionema, Cochlearia, Camelina. In: DAVIS, P. H. (ed.), Fl. Turkey 1: 193 - 493." type="journal article" year="1965">HEDGE (1965: 323)</bibRefCitation>
reduced the species to synonymy of 
<emphasis box="[245,403,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName box="[245,400,1700,1724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositifolia">A. oppositifolia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
both of which species are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName authority="(AL-SHEHBAZ, 2014)" baseAuthorityName="AL-SHEHBAZ" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[288,604,1732,1756]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[288,368,1732,1755]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">Noccaea</emphasis>
(AL-SHEHBAZ, 2014)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="143.[135,787,1539,1884]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
Although the publication of 
<taxonomicName box="[472,664,1764,1788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Eunomia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis box="[472,664,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">Eunomia rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was attributed to 
<bibRefCitation author="TCHIHATCHEFF, P. DE" box="[217,461,1795,1820]" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" refId="ref144095" refString="TCHIHATCHEFF, P. DE (1860). Asie Mineure description physique, statistique et archeologique de cette contree. Botanique 1. Paris." type="book" year="1860">TCHIHATCHEFF (1860)</bibRefCitation>
, the name was a 
<emphasis box="[641,786,1796,1820]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">
nomen 
<taxonomicName box="[714,786,1796,1820]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Sisymbrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="143" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudum">nudum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and, therefore, its publication ought to be attributed to Boissier in 
<emphasis box="[164,328,1860,1884]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="143">Flora Orientalis</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
